headline: KLM loses Delta and Air France as ground services customer
summary: The airlines have told KLM they are looking for an alternative ground handling partner at Schiphol, one of Europe's busiest airports, it said.  "This decision has immediate operational implications for KLM, particularly for the ground services department," KLM said in a statement.
